rComments: DO NOT TAKE A CLASS WITH HER! Her notes made no sense (all just random symbols/abbreviations that she didnt explain) Even people in other sections couldnt understand them. Rushed through material, couldnt answer simple questions. We werent at all prepared for the midterm. I'm sure shes nice as a person, but not as a prof. Your GPA will hurt.

Seems to know the material well but explains it in a way that isn't easy to understand without already having a background in stats. Some advice: read the textbook before class or you will get lost in her explanations.

Does not communicate well with her students, explains in such a way that makes the class extremely confusing, very big words, long solutions to the most simple/basic logic problems. Buy the textbook!!!!
Terrible prof, extremely boring, don't take her class
She is incredibly incoherent, and talks way too long about things that are not important. If possible, get another Prof. !

She is such a frazzled person! Jumps from one subject to another as they enter her mind. Does not know how to speak in simple, non-mathematical terms which makes the material super confusing. My textbook is now my best friend.

Only two weeks in and yet she seems to be an absolutely terrible prof. While lecturing, she ignores all students: It's just her and the blackboard. Also speaks in mathematical/complicated lingo rather than trying to teach the class as if we're human.. Drop this class ASAP if you ever find out she's your prof, or else be prepared to teach yourself.

Le cours est difficile car elle n'expliquait pas beaucoup les exemples mais plutôt les concepts.  Puis le fait que l'algèbre linéaire est différent et nouveau pour un étudiant en première année, on a besoin de plus d'exemples.  Les examens sont plus difficiles que les autres sections et la moyenne est plus basse.
